title: add hasDni key to DniOrNameView
message:
add hasDni key to DniOrNameView

Before this commit, DniOrNameView was only adding values to
the map for the DNI and name EditTexts. This left open the
possibility that someone might enter both DNI and name by
toggling the RadioButtons, in which case sending the map
wouldn't make it clear which they actually wanted. To remedy
this, this commit adds a hasDni key that also indicates which
RadioButton was selected. It adds tests and updates all the
affected Activities.

title: custom attributes for SelectOneView
message:
custom attributes for SelectOneView

I had originally created a SelectOneView that allows labels
and values to be specified in XML. So say that you had dog,
cat, fish displayed to the user, the view would return a
d, c, or f as the "value" to be saved in the DB. Very similar
to how ODK Collect selects work. I exposed this to allow it
to be specified in XML, so you could add attributes to your
SelectOneView tag like custom:labels="@array/labels".
Unfortunately, it looks like Robolectric can't handle this,
and custom attributes cause it to fail (Bug #1102). So, I
am going to have to pull this out and specify it only in
code. However, I am committing this so that I can use it for
a test case later if I choose to try and fix the bug in
Robolectric.

title: add SelectOneView with tests
message:
add SelectOneView with tests

SelectOneView lets you specify a list of labels and values,
much like an ODK Collect select one, to present a list of
choices to a user. This commit adds that feature, using a
Spinner, and lets you specify both lists in XML.

message: Bug fix: Position the image in the center of the screen only for question that do not have multiple choices.

title: Improved error-handling during form save: (Α) Upon save, validate the form using…
message: Improved error-handling during form save: (Α) Upon save, validate the form using a new (memory-wise)  position index, in order not to mess with the current form state. Change the current form index only upon a validation error. This avoids a crash when the user cancels the saving and swipes left. (B) All .xml files (including the save points) are now saved with RandomAccessFile that guaranties that the file will be written synchronously, so nothing will be lost upon a crash. (C) Do not swallow save failures; tunnel the actual error message back to the screen for troubleshooting purposes. (D) Cancelling the save process during form validation actually cancels the process and nothing is saved.

title: Improved error-handling: Instead of letting the whole app crash, display a…
message: Improved error-handling: Instead of letting the whole app crash, display a user-friendly error message to the user so that the form-design error can be corrected. Such form-design errors include the case where there is a reference to a repeated field (a) outside the repeat, and (b) without using indexed-repeat().

title: Improved error-handling: Added the exception message in the HEAD request too and…
message: Improved error-handling: Added the exception message in the HEAD request too and also replaced "exception.toString()" with "exception.getMessage()" which is much friendlier.

title: SurveyCTO's external app usage extension features: (1) Being able to pass other…
message: SurveyCTO's external app usage extension features: (1) Being able to pass other field values in, as other extras and (2) being able to have the external app update multiple fields (e.g., return multiple values to update several fields in a group). See docs/external-apps/tutorial.txt for the a quick tutorial for each of these features.

title: Improved error handling: Make sure that the downloaded form is not "installed"…
message: Improved error handling: Make sure that the downloaded form is not "installed" until everything has been downloaded and the user has not cancelled the process in any stage (form download, media download, form parsing). Moreover download everything to a temp location and move to the final location only if no error occurs. The installation of the form is performed at the very end.

title: android has localization bugs representing decimals as ',' instead of '.' for…
message: android has localization bugs representing decimals as ',' instead of '.' for other languages.  It prints the decimal as ',', but the edittext doesn't allow ',' as a valid entry.  as a workaround we convert all ',' to '.' and only allow '.' in our decimal widget.  fixes issue 366

title: Fixes the bug where a swipe that brings up a constraint triggers a 'long-press'…
message:
Fixes the bug where a swipe that brings up a constraint triggers a 'long-press' on a view.  The problem was that the 'up' action is handled by the activity, so the view never sees it and pops the long-press menu.  We fixed it by calling cancelLongPress() when we notice the user scrolling.

This checkin also removes our home-grown gesture detector and uses android's built in, instead.
